# Flutter Development Rules

## State Management
- ALWAYS use `flutter_hooks` (HookWidget) instead of StatefulWidget where possible
- Prefer hooks like `useTextEditingController`, `useState`, `useEffect`, `useMemoized` over manual state management
- Only use StatefulWidget when hooks cannot handle the specific use case (rare)
- use riverpod with code generation notation for 

## Flutter API Usage
- NEVER use deprecated `withOpacity()` method
- ALWAYS use `withValues(alpha: value)` instead of `withOpacity(value)`
- Use `withValues(alpha: 0.5)` instead of `withOpacity(0.5)`

## Code Style
- Use `const` constructors whenever possible
- Prefer composition over inheritance